      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>This is a general record for any possible constellation of the Miracles of Takla Hāymānot.</p>
            <p>The full version as witnessed e.g. by <ref type="mss" corresp="IVorlov35"/> contains up to 72 miracles divided into three cycles of 22 miracles and a homily each,  <ref target="#Birth">the Cycle for the Birth on <date>22 Tahsas</date></ref>,  <ref target="#Concept">the Cycle for Conception on <date>24  Maggābit</date></ref>, <ref target="#Trans">the Cycle for the Translation of his relics on <date>12 Gǝnbot</date></ref>, in addition to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5778MirTaklaHaymanotSabal"></ref>. Other witnesses may include any subset, e.g. <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient723"></ref> with 44 + 2 miracles, <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet110"></ref>, with 34 miracles, <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr16 "></ref> with 21 miracles, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient721"></ref> and <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient722"></ref>, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient724"></ref> with 16 miracles each, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient727"></ref> with 18 miracles, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient728"></ref> with 20 miracles, etc. </p>
         </abstract>
